        "title":"Greenvolt to develop 400 MW battery storage in Poland in 2026",
        "subtitle":"\n              (Montel) Portuguese renewable energy firm Greenvolt plans to launch two battery energy storage systems (BESS) in Poland in Q1 2026.\n            ",
        "body":"\nChinese company BYD will build and operate the two BESS projects, totalling 400 MW in capacity, Greenvolt said in a statement on Monday.\nThe Turosn Koscielna and Nowa Wies Elcka battery storage facilities in northeast Poland will each be able to store 800 MWh of electricity.\nGreenvolt has secured capacity payments of PLN 244.90\/kW (EUR 58.53\/kW) annually for 17 years from the Polish state, starting from 2028.\nThe Lisbon-headquartered company plans to build a further 800 MW of battery storage capacity in Poland by 2028 following a win in a capacity market auction last year.\n",
